section.para:
The Premises Editor project was undertaken to provide;




			A useful documentation tool for livestock producers and
			infrastructure providers;





			A low cost documentation solution for deployment to both large and
			small scale livestock operations;





			An industry standard format for livestock event history
			inter-exchange.

Animals and Events are added to Tracker Premises Documents;




			Individually by the user via the Premise Document Editor, Premises Views, and the
			Properties Viewer;





			In bulk, by the user, through Tracker's Bulk Event Processing Utilities;





			In real time, from tag ID readers, through the Tracker Readers Feature



		    See Editing Premises Documents for details on
		    Tracker Readers Feature and Premises document editing.

Animal Document Templates have the following characteristics;




			Animal Documents contain a default Animal, a Tag and a set of representative 
			events;





			If a Tag is included as a child element of the Animal Element, the Tag/@idNumber 
			is not considered significant and is ignored;





			Animal Documents are persisted in files with a *.animal extension;





			All Animal Document Event Elements are significant and will be copied to the 
			specified Animal or set Animals in the Premises Document;





			Date Time attributes of Animal Document Event Elements are considered significant
		    and are copied to the Event Elements that are added to the specified Animal or set of Animal Elements in the Premises Document. The following are special exceptions;




						When a tags file name uses the format yyMMddHHmmss.tags. The Date 
						Time attributes of all Event Elements copied to the Premises Document
					    will assume the time stamp of of the date pattern
						yyMMddHHss
						. For example the tags file 060409131111.Tags will set the Date Time 
						attribute of all Event Elements to 2006-04-09T13:11:11;





						When the date of an event in an Animal Document Template is set to 
						a year earlier than 1000 AD, then the date of the event copied to 
						the Premises Document is set to the current time the Event.







					Bulk loading of events is only applicable to the the Tracker Editor, when transaction Events and Animals are added to Premises Documents using the Tracker Transaction processing facility, the Event Element added to the Premises Document will always have the Date Time attributes set to the current time.

To add a series of events to an animal or set of animals in a Premises 
Document select the animal or animals and invoke a popup menu item;




			Right click on the Animal to get the top level popup menu;





			Select the 'Tracker' menu item to get the Tracker popup menu;





			Select 'Add Template Events to Selected Animals' to bring up a 
			selection window to select a Template;





			Choose an Animal Document Template containing the set of events 
			you wish to add the animal.
